Author-Name: David K. Whitcomb 
Author-Workplace-Name: Automated Trading Desk, Inc. and Rutgers University 
Title: Market Maker Quotation Behavior and Pretrade Transparency 
Abstract:
 We examine the impact of differing levels of pretrade transparency on the
 quotation behavior of Nasdaq market makers. We find that market makers are
 more likely to quote on odd ticks, and to actively narrow the spread, when
 they can do so anonymously by posting limit orders on Electronic
 Communication Networks (ECNs). From a public policy perspective, our
 findings suggest that making the level of pretrade transparency on Nasdaq
 more opaque by allowing anonymous quotes could improve price competition
 and narrow spreads further. Copyright 2003 by the American Finance Association. 
